The best approach is to use the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package — it's battle-tested and already wraps all of `File.*`, `Directory.*`, `Path.*`, etc.

## Setup

**1. Install packages:**
```bash
dotnet add <YourProject> package System.IO.Abstractions
dotnet add <YourTestProject> package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

**2. Register in DI (`Program.cs` or `Startup.cs`):**
```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

**3. Inject `IFileSystem` into your classes:**
```csharp
public class MyService(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    public void SaveData(string path, string content)
        => fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(path, content);

    public string LoadData(string path)
        => fileSystem.File.ReadAllText(path);

    public bool EnsureDirectory(string path)
        => fileSystem.Directory.Exists(path);
}
```

**4. Test with `MockFileSystem`:**
```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem(new Dictionary<string, MockFileData>
{
    { "/data/config.json", new MockFileData("{\"key\": \"value\"}") }
});

var service = new MyService(mockFs);

// Test ReadAllText
Assert.Equal("{\"key\": \"value\"}", service.LoadData("/data/config.json"));

// Test WriteAllText
service.SaveData("/data/output.txt", "hello");
Assert.Equal("hello", mockFs.File.ReadAllText("/data/output.txt"));

// Test Directory.Exists
Assert.True(service.EnsureDirectory("/data"));
Assert.False(service.EnsureDirectory("/nonexistent"));
```

## Why this over a custom wrapper?

| | `System.IO.Abstractions` | Custom `IFileService` |
|---|---|---|
| Coverage | All `File`, `Directory`, `Path` APIs | Only what you wrap |
| Maintenance | Community-maintained | You maintain it |
| Test helpers | `MockFileSystem` included | You write your own mocks |
| Adoption cost | One NuGet install | Interface + implementation + tests |

**Key rule:** Don't wrap every `File.*` method speculatively — only inject `IFileSystem` into classes that actually use those three calls. The interface is comprehensive, but your classes only call what they need.

